An OpenAPI for EVE Online

      • get /alliances/

        • List all alliances

        Implementation Notes

        List all active player alliances

        Alternate route: /v1/alliances/

        Alternate route: /legacy/alliances/

        Alternate route: /dev/alliances/

        This route is cached for up to 3600 seconds

        Response Class (Status 200)

        List of Alliance IDs

        • Model
        • Example Value
        get_alliances_ok [
        integer:

        200 ok integer

        ] 
        {
  "application/json": [
    99000001,
    99000002
  ]
}


        Headers

        Header Description Type Other
        Cache-Control The caching mechanism used string
        Expires RFC7231 formatted datetime string string
        Last-Modified RFC7231 formatted datetime string string

        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type

        The server name you would like data from

        		 query string

        Client identifier, takes precedence over headers

        		 query string

        Client identifier, takes precedence over User-Agent

        		 header string

        Internal server error

      • get /alliances/names/

        • Get alliance names

        Implementation Notes

        Resolve a set of alliance IDs to alliance names

        Alternate route: /v1/alliances/names/

        Alternate route: /legacy/alliances/names/

        This route is cached for up to 3600 seconds

        Response Class (Status 200)

        List of id/name associations

        • Model
        • Example Value
        get_alliances_names_ok [
        get_alliances_names_200_ok
        ]
        get_alliances_names_200_ok {
        alliance_id (integer):

        alliance_id integer

        ,
        alliance_name (string):

        alliance_name string

        } 
        {
  "application/json": [
    {
      "alliance_id": 1000171,
      "alliance_name": "Republic University"
    }
  ]
}


        Headers

        Header Description Type Other
        Cache-Control The caching mechanism used string
        Expires RFC7231 formatted datetime string string
        Last-Modified RFC7231 formatted datetime string string

        Parameters

        Parameter Value Description Parameter Type Data Type

        A comma separated list of alliance IDs

                 		query Array[long]

      • get /alliances/{alliance_id}/

        • Get alliance information

        Implementation Notes

        Public information about an alliance

        Alternate route: /v2/alliances/{alliance_id}/

        This route is cached for up to 3600 seconds

        Response Class (Status 200)

        Public data about an alliance

        • Model
        • Example Value
        get_alliances_alliance_id_ok {
        alliance_name (string):

        the full name of the alliance

        ,
        date_founded (string):

        date_founded string

        ,
        executor_corp (integer, optional):

        the executor corporation ID, if this alliance is not closed

        ,
        ticker (string):

        the short name of the alliance

        } 
        {
  "application/json": {
    "alliance_name": "C C P Alliance",
    "date_founded": "2016-06-26T21:00:00Z",
    "executor_corp": 98356193,
    "ticker": "<C C P>"
  }
}

      • get /alliances/{alliance_id}/icons/

        • Get alliance icon

        Implementation Notes

        Get the icon urls for a alliance

        Alternate route: /v1/alliances/{alliance_id}/icons/

        Alternate route: /legacy/alliances/{alliance_id}/icons/

        Alternate route: /dev/alliances/{alliance_id}/icons/

        Response Class (Status 200)

        Icon URLs for the given alliance id and server

        • Model

        ,

    "px64x64": "https://imageserver.eveonline.com/Alliance/503818424_64.png"
  }
}

      • post /characters/{character_id}/assets/locations/

        • Get character asset locations

        Implementation Notes

        Return locations for a set of item ids, which you can get from character assets endpoint. Coordinates for items in hangars or stations are set to (0,0,0)

        Alternate route: /v1/characters/{character_id}/assets/locations/

        Alternate route: /legacy/characters/{character_id}/assets/locations/

        Alternate route: /dev/characters/{character_id}/assets/locations/

        • esi-assets.read_assets.v1

        Response Class (Status 200)

        List of asset locations

        • Model
        • Example Value

        ,
        z (number):

        z number

        } 
        {
  "application/json": [
    {
      "item_id": 12345,
      "x": 1.2,
      "y": 2.3,
      "z": -3.4
    }
  ]
}

      • post /characters/{character_id}/assets/names/

        • Get character asset names

        Implementation Notes

        Return names for a set of item ids, which you can get from character assets endpoint. Typically used for items that can customize names, like containers or ships.

        Alternate route: /v1/characters/{character_id}/assets/names/

        Alternate route: /legacy/characters/{character_id}/assets/names/

        Alternate route: /dev/characters/{character_id}/assets/names/

      • get /characters/{character_id}/bookmarks/

        • List bookmarks

        Implementation Notes

        List your character's personal bookmarks

        Alternate route: /v1/characters/{character_id}/bookmarks/

        Alternate route: /legacy/characters/{character_id}/bookmarks/

        Alternate route: /dev/characters/{character_id}/bookmarks/

        This route is cached for up to 3600 seconds

        • esi-bookmarks.read_character_bookmarks.v1

        Response Class (Status 200)

        A list of bookmarks

        • Model
        • Example Value
        get_characters_character_id_bookmarks_ok [
        get_characters_character_id_bookmarks_200_ok
        ]
        get_characters_character_id_bookmarks_200_ok {

      • get /characters/{character_id}/calendar/

        • List calendar event summaries

        Implementation Notes

        Get 50 event summaries from the calendar. If no from_event ID is given, the resource will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from now. If a from_event ID is specified, it will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from after that event.

        ,
        role (string):

        If a character is invited with the fleet_commander role, neither wing_id or squad_id should be specified. If a character is invited with the wing_commander role, only wing_id should be specified. If a character is invited with the squad_commander role, both wing_id and squad_id should be specified. If a character is invited with the squad_member role, wing_id and squad_id should either both be specified or not specified at all. If they aren’t specified, the invited character will join any squad with available positions.

        The state of this incursion

      • get /sovereignty/structures/

        • List sovereignty structures

        Implementation Notes

        Shows sovereignty data for structures.

        Alternate route: /v1/sovereignty/structures/

        Alternate route: /legacy/sovereignty/structures/

        Alternate route: /dev/sovereignty/structures/

        This route is cached for up to 120 seconds

        Response Class (Status 200)

        A list of sovereignty structures

        • Model
        • Example Value
        get_sovereignty_structures_ok [
        get_sovereignty_structures_200_ok
        ]
        get_sovereignty_structures_200_ok {
        alliance_id (integer):

        The alliance that owns the structure.

        ,
        solar_system_id (integer):

        Solar system in which the structure is located.

        ,
        structure_id (integer):

        Unique item ID for this structure.

        ,
        structure_type_id (integer):

        A reference to the type of structure this is.

        ,
        vulnerability_occupancy_level (number, optional):

        The occupancy level for the next or current vulnerability window. This takes into account all development indexes and capital system bonuses. Also known as Activity Defense Multiplier from in the client. It increases the time that attackers must spend using their entosis links on the structure.

        ,
        vulnerable_end_time (string, optional):

        The time at which the next or current vulnerability window ends. At the end of a vulnerability window the next window is recalculated and locked in along with the vulnerabilityOccupancyLevel. If the structure is not in 100% entosis control of the defender, it will go in to 'overtime' and stay vulnerable for as long as that situation persists. Only once the defenders have 100% entosis control and has the vulnerableEndTime passed does the vulnerability interval expire and a new one is calculated.

        ,
        vulnerable_start_time (string, optional):

        The next time at which the structure will become vulnerable. Or the start time of the current window if current time is between this and vulnerableEndTime.

        } 
        {
  "application/json": [
    {
      "alliance_id": 498125261,
      "solar_system_id": 30000570,
      "structure_id": 1018253388776,
      "structure_type_id": 32226,
      "vulnerability_occupancy_level": 2,
      "vulnerable_end_time": "2016-10-29T05:30:00Z",
      "vulnerable_start_time": "2016-10-28T20:30:00Z"
    }
  ]
}

        • Example Value

        ,

        allied corporations or alliances, each object contains either corporation_id or alliance_id

        object
        Max. Items:10000
        ,
        declared (string):

        Time that the war was declared

        ,
        defender (get_wars_war_id_defender):

        The defending corporation or alliance that declared this war, only contains either corporation_id or alliance_id

        ,

        ,

        ID of the specified war

        ,

        Was the war declared mutual by both parties

        ,
        open_for_allies (boolean):

        Is the war currently open for allies or not

        Time when the war started and both sides could shoot each other

        ,
        isk_destroyed (number):

        ISK value of ships the defender has killed

        ,
        ships_killed (integer):

        The number of ships the defender has killed

        }
